treatment_vec <- c("high food - low temp", "low food - low temp", "high food - high temp", "low food - high temp" )
treatment_col <- c(c("darkblue", "skyblue", "darkred", "firebrick1"))
data <- df_weight_limited %>% 
  select(spiderlingID, motherID, treatment, urb_cat, weight_start, weight_point1, weight_point2)
colnames(data) <- c("spiderlingID", "motherID", "treatment", "urb_cat", "w0", "w1", "w2")

data_long <- data %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("w0", "w1", "w2"), 
               names_to = "time", 
               names_prefix = "w", 
               values_to = "weight")

data_long <- data_long %>%
  mutate(time_numeric = case_when(
    time == "0" ~ 0,
    time == "1" ~ 4,
    time == "2" ~ 19
  ))

data_long <- data_long %>%
  mutate(treatment_name = case_when(
    treatment == "T1" ~ "high food - low temp",
    treatment == "T2" ~ "low food - low temp",
    treatment == "T3" ~ "high food - high temp",
    treatment == "T4" ~ "low food - high temp"
  ))

t_col <- c("darkred", "darkblue", "firebrick1", "skyblue")
data_long$treatment_name <- as.factor(data_long$treatment_name)
p<-ggplot(data_long, aes(x = time_numeric, y = weight, group = spiderlingID, color = urb_cat)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(~treatment_name)+
  labs(title = "growth curve per spiderling",
       x = "time (weeks)",
       y = "weight (mg)",
       color = "urb_cat") +
  scale_colour_manual(values=urb.col2, name="urbanisation category \nmother spider")+
  theme_bw()
p
g <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(p))
stript <- which(grepl('strip-t', g$layout$name))
fills <- scales::alpha(t_col, 0.40)
k <- 1
for (i in stript) {
  j <- which(grepl('rect', g$grobs[[i]]$grobs[[1]]$childrenOrder))
  g$grobs[[i]]$grobs[[1]]$children[[j]]$gp$fill <- fills[k]
  k <- k+1
}
grid::grid.draw(g)

data <- df_weight %>% 
  select(spiderlingID, motherID, treatment, urb_cat, weight_start, weight_point1)
colnames(data) <- c("spiderlingID", "motherID", "treatment", "urb_cat", "w0", "w1")

data_long <- data %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("w0", "w1"), 
               names_to = "time", 
               names_prefix = "w", 
               values_to = "weight")

data_long <- data_long %>%
  mutate(time_numeric = case_when(
    time == "0" ~ 0,
    time == "1" ~ 4,
  ))

data_long <- data_long %>%
  mutate(treatment_name = case_when(
    treatment == "T1" ~ "high food - low temp",
    treatment == "T2" ~ "low food - low temp",
    treatment == "T3" ~ "high food - high temp",
    treatment == "T4" ~ "low food - high temp"
  ))
t_col <- c("darkred", "darkblue", "firebrick1", "skyblue")
data_long$treatment_name <- as.factor(data_long$treatment_name) 

p<-ggplot(data_long, aes(x = time_numeric, y = weight, group = spiderlingID, color = urb_cat)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(~treatment_name)+
  labs(title = "growth curve per spiderling",
       x = "time (weeks)",
       y = "weight (mg)",
       color = "urb_cat") +
  scale_colour_manual(values=urb.col2, name="urbanisation category \nmother spider")+
  theme_bw()
p
g <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(p))
stript <- which(grepl('strip-t', g$layout$name))
fills <- scales::alpha(t_col, 0.40)
k <- 1
for (i in stript) {
  j <- which(grepl('rect', g$grobs[[i]]$grobs[[1]]$childrenOrder))
  g$grobs[[i]]$grobs[[1]]$children[[j]]$gp$fill <- fills[k]
  k <- k+1
}
grid::grid.draw(g)
